# Concise Comments

Code comments must be short and carry only useful information that the code cannot convey.

## Rule

- No narration of what the code does. No "Import X", "Define Y", "Return Z", "Handle the error".
- No essays, no restating the task, no explaining the change you're making.
- No invented comment tag prefixes (e.g. `ponytail:`, `NOTE:`, `HACK:`). Plain prose only, and only when it earns the line.
- No copying long explanations from other platforms into web ports.
- If a comment isn't earning its line, delete it.

## Why

Verbose comments are noise. They drift from the code, hide real intent, and waste review time.

## Examples

Bad:

```ts
// website `useMe` reads `state.auth`.
// (website store exposes `state.auth`, no useSensor) and LoadCurrentCustomer (website
// has no Adapter class, so it uses $$_dataAdapter directly).
```

Good:

```ts
// website `useMe` reads `state.auth`.
```

Best: no comment if the code is obvious.

## Scope

Applies to every file under the workspace, all platforms (website, cpanel, backend, docs).
